Gary<br>
The worst nightmare they could have, was droppping a load on their own troops. Many, many times I felt the air sucked out from around me and felt pity for those that were under the explosion as it went out.<br><br>
I loved it when they would circle overhead after they had successfully dropped their bombs and just sort of hang there and then just drop their wings Goodby, and disappear into the sky.<br><br>
Those were some proud moments.<br><br>
ALL you pilots out there, and all you corpsmen out there, <br><br>
Thank You, 
